How to use tiled2unity (FOR LINUX ONLY; Windows and Mac (I think) both have better-looking converters):

In case Tiled2UnityLite.cs isn't compiled, do:
    mcs -r:System.Xml.Linq,System.Drawing Tiled2UnityLite.cs

And now, just do:
    cd <Tiled2Unity executable location>
    mono ./Tiled2UnityLite.exe <tiled_map_file> <output_folder_in_project>


Examples:
    cd "/home/susanna/Documents/coding projects/unity/Tiled2Unity"
    mono ./Tiled2UnityLite.exe "/home/susanna/Documents/coding projects/unity/LearningUnity/Assets/tiled/test2.tmx" "/home/susanna/Documents/coding projects/unity/LearningUnity/Assets/Tiled2Unity"

    cd "/home/susanna/Documents/coding projects/unity/Tiled2Unity"
    mono ./Tiled2UnityLite.exe "/home/susanna/Documents/coding projects/unity/Tiled2Unity/maps/test_maps/testmap1.tmx" "/home/susanna/Documents/coding projects/unity/GBT/Assets/Tiled2Unity"
